Doubtless the main object of the innovation was to enable testators to bequeath a general usufruct over all their property. That the right was not a usufruct proper is clear from the text (‘ nec usufructus est ’ fragm. Vat. 46, ‘ non id effectum, ut pecuniae ususfructus proprie esset’ Dig. 7. 5. 2. 1).
